K Nearest Neighbor¶

In [62]:
wcss=[]
In [63]:
for k in range(1,11):
    k_mean=KMeans(n_clusters= k, init='k-means++', max_iter=300, n_init=10,random_state=46)
    k_mean.fit(X)
    wcss.append(k_mean.inertia_)
